{{Infobox video game | title= Kaptain Brawe: A Brawe New World | image= | caption= | developer= [[Cateia Games]] | publisher= | director = | producer = | designer = | programmer = | artist = | writer = | series= Kaptain Brawe | engine= | released= 2011 | genre= [[Adventure game|Adventure]], [[Hidden object game|hidden object]], [[Puzzle game|puzzle]] | modes= [[Single player]] | platforms= [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Windows Phone]], [[Mac OS X]], [[IOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] }}
'''Kaptain Brawe: A Brawe New World''' is a [[point and click|point n' click]] adventure video game developed by [[Cateia Games]]. It was released in 2011 for [[Windows XP|Microsoft Windows]], [[Windows Phone]], [[Macintosh|Mac]], [[IOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]]. It follows the adventures of ''Kaptain Brawe'', a Space Police officer who embarks on a journey filled with quests, conspiracies and general chaos, as he follows the lead of two kidnapped alien scientists.<ref name="cateia">{{cite web|url=http://www.cateia.com/games/games.php?id=23|title=Kaptain Brawe: A Brawe New World - Cateia Games|publisher=cateia.com|accessdate=2014-12-06}}</ref>
==Reception== The PC version holds a score of 69 based on 6 reviews on [[Metacritic]]<ref name="metacritic">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/kaptain-brawe-a-brave-new-world|title=Kaptain Brawe: A Brave New World for PC Reviews - Metacritic|publisher=metacritic.com|accessdate=2014-12-06}}</ref> and 78.79% based on 4 reviews on [[GameRankings]].<ref name="gamerankings">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/pc/612412-kaptain-brawe-a-brave-new-world/index.html|title=Kaptain Brawe: A Brave New World for PC - GameRankings|publisher=gamerankings.com|accessdate=2014-12-06}}</ref> The iOS version holds a score of 76 based on 8 reviews on Metacritic, and 75.83% on Gamerankings.<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/kaptain-brawe-a-brawe-new-world</ref><ref>http://www.gamerankings.com/iphone/653719-kaptain-brawe-a-brawe-new-world/index.html</ref>
==Sequel== A sequel titled Kaptain Brawe 2: A Space Travesty launched on Kickstarter with the goal of obtaining 150,000$ and was to be written by [[Steve Ince]] and designed in part by [[Bill Tiller]].<ref>https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2014/05/23/adwenture-time-kaptain-brawe-2-a-space-travesty/#more-208893</ref><ref>https://www.hcl.hr/vijest/kaptain-brawe-2-se-vratio-na-kickstarter-43017/</ref> However it never reached its goal and was cancelled as a result.
